#: ../../../source/docs/porting/asyncify.rst:259
msgid "More on ``ASYNCIFY_IMPORTS``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/asyncify.rst:261
msgid ""
"As in the above example, you can add JS functions that do an async operation "
"but look synchronous from the perspective of C. If you don't use "
"``EM_ASYNC_JS``, it's vital to add such methods to :ref:`ASYNCIFY_IMPORTS`. "
"That list of imports is the list of imports to the Wasm module that the "
"Asyncify instrumentation must be aware of. Giving it that list tells it that "
"all other JS calls will **not** do an async operation, which lets it not add "
"overhead where it isn't needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/asyncify.rst:268
msgid ""
"If the import is not inside ``env`` the full path must be specified, for "
"example, ``ASYNCIFY_IMPORTS=wasi_snapshot_preview1.fd_write``"
msgstr ""

